{"tid":618428,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"一名中國科學家　因偷種子竊密予中國人員　於美國被判十年監禁","createTime":"2018-04-05T22:15:53.000Z","updateTime":"2018-04-30T04:37:13.000Z","uid":147314,"like":82,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":42,"replies":[{"pid":"a940e34222afc0a2fb2961082d0ce29a8254d0c8","tid":618428,"uid":147314,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:15:53.000Z","msg":"盜取知識產權不僅傷害到被竊取的公司　同時危害到美國國家安全<br />\n<br />\n盜水稻種子 中國學者涉竊密 判囚121個月<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://gdb.voanews.com/D909335D-D919-4212-9615-CA1120E72745_cx0_cy9_cw0_w600_r1_s.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fgdb.voanews.com%2FD909335D-D919-4212-9615-CA1120E72745_cx0_cy9_cw0_w600_r1_s.jpg&h=405fe7b1&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n一名中國科學家日前因涉嫌從堪薩斯州的一家生物製藥研究中心盜取多種水稻種子樣本而被捕控以共謀盜取商業機密罪，4日被德州北區聯邦法院判以121個月監禁。<br />\n<br />\n51歲的中國科學家張維強(Weiqiang Zhang，音譯)從瀋陽農業大學農學碩士畢業，並獲得路易斯安那州立大學(Louisiana State University)博士學位，持有綠卡，居住在堪薩斯州Manhattan市，在該州Junction市的生物製藥公司 Ventria Bioscience擔任水稻培養員。該公司主要研發重組了人類蛋白的基因水稻項目，研發產品主要用於醫療和醫藥領域。<br />\n<br />\n根據法庭文件，張維強在未授權情況下獲得幾百種Ventria公司生產的水稻種子樣本，並將這些樣本存放在自己家中。這些種子的研發目的主要是用來生產血液中的人血清白蛋白或乳鐵蛋白，Ventria多年來花費上百萬元用來進行相關研究，並用及嚴密的方式來保存這些種子。"},{"pid":"3fed14e82f8b8d23ff2d8132ed3ed8d665115b39","tid":618428,"uid":147314,"like":50,"dislike":0,"score":50,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:16:29.000Z","msg":"2013年夏天，一群來自中國研究中心的人員到張維強家中拜訪，張開車帶他們參觀了位於俄亥俄州、密蘇里州和愛荷華州的多家實驗中心。2013年8月該行人離境前，美國海關及邊境保護局(U.S. Customs and Border Protection)在他們的行李箱中發現屬於Ventria公司的水稻種。<br />\n<br />\n之後張維強被捕，於2017年2月15日在堪薩斯州聯邦法院被控共謀盜取商業機密罪、共謀跨州運輸贓物罪和跨州運輸贓物罪。本月4日，法官判其121個月徒刑。<br />\n<br />\n檢方對此表示，盜取知識產權不僅傷害到被竊取的公司，同時危害到美國國家安全，保護知識產權被盜及防止其被外國利益濫用對美國國家安全至關重要。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://udn.com/news/story/6813/3071052\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fudn.com%2Fnews%2Fstory%2F6813%2F3071052&d=Qkcn4anxcNjNLEy4KtNlZQEk2Noh57F05xbgvjQdsX8%3D&h=ca0b5a19\" target=\"_blank\">https://udn.com/news/story/6813/3071052</a>"},{"pid":"4d952a2bcb5fc9d4874e6c3204c197f1fa87b55f","tid":618428,"uid":104443,"like":41,"dislike":2,"score":39,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:17:38.000Z","msg":"點解唔死刑<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"fbff8f540d906a67ccba9713c3fce853f7c1fa33","tid":618428,"uid":62599,"like":12,"dislike":1,"score":11,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:17:59.000Z","msg":"正一賤種<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n食屎狗<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b78a901c08c6540b5a81ab8e8c819943acb5988f","tid":618428,"uid":104443,"like":33,"dislike":1,"score":32,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:18:55.000Z","msg":"同埋唔好貼相得唔得，唔想望到啲咁醜嘅人"},{"pid":"2be4132561b58c45d4ff50e32a044360f2138415","tid":618428,"uid":147314,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:19:48.000Z","msg":"Chinese scientist gets 10 years in U.S. prison over theft of GMO rice<br />\n<br />\n(Reuters) - A Chinese scientist in Kansas was sentenced on Wednesday to more than 10 years in a federal prison for conspiring to steal samples of a variety of genetically engineered rice seeds from a U.S. research facility, the U.S. Justice Department said.<br />\n<br />\nU.S. District Court Judge Carlos Murguia in the District of Kansas sentenced Weiqiang Zhang, 51, a Chinese national living in Manhattan, Kansas, to 121 months in prison.<br />\n<br />\nZhang was convicted in February 2017 on three counts, including conspiracy to steal trade secrets and interstate transportation of stolen property, the department said in a statement.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Today&rsquo;s sentence demonstrates the significant consequences awaiting those who would steal trade secrets from American companies,&rdquo; said John P. Cronan, DOJ&rsquo;s acting assistant attorney general.<br />\n<br />\nNeither Zhang nor his attorney could be reached for comment on Wednesday.<br />\n<br />\nZhang, who holds a doctorate from Louisiana State University, worked as a rice breeder for Kansas-based Ventria Bioscience Inc, which develops genetically programmed rice used in the therapeutic and medical fields. He stole hundreds of rice seeds produced by Ventria and stored them at his Manhattan residence, the statement said.<br />\n<br />\nChina had long banned commercial growing of GMO grains due to public opposition to the technology. But last year, ChemChina&rsquo;s purchase of Swiss agrochemical and seed company Syngenta was seen by market analysts and industry experts as a sign that the country was becoming more open to production of genetically modified crops.<br />\n<br />\nIn recent years, U.S. law enforcement officials have urged agriculture executives and security officers to increase their vigilance and report suspicious activity involving farm products, citing a growing economic and national security threat to the sector.<br />\n<br />\nReporting by P.J. Huffstutter and Tom Polansek in Chicago; Editing by Matthew Lewis<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/us-kansas-court-china/chinese-scientist-gets-10-years-in-u-s-prison-over-theft-of-gmo-rice-idUSKCN1HB36A\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-kansas-court-china%2Fchinese-scientist-gets-10-years-in-u-s-prison-over-theft-of-gmo-rice-idUSKCN1HB36A&d=Qkcn4anxcNjNLEy4KtNlZQEk2Noh57F05xbgvjQdsX8%3D&h=00530f30\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-kansas-court-china%2Fchinese-scientist-gets-10-years-in-u-s-prison-over-theft-of-gmo-rice-idUSKCN1HB36A&h=4d14186d\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.reuters.com/article/us-kansas-court-china/chinese-scientist-gets-10-years-in-u-s-prison-over-theft-of-gmo-rice-idUSKCN1HB36A</a>"},{"pid":"ececcedcb22fd3cb0591305155519ec167c33235","tid":618428,"uid":147314,"like":22,"dislike":0,"score":22,"quote":{"pid":"b78a901c08c6540b5a81ab8e8c819943acb5988f","tid":618428,"uid":104443,"like":33,"dislike":1,"score":32,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:18:55.000Z","msg":"同埋唔好貼相得唔得，唔想望到啲咁醜嘅人"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:21:30.000Z","msg":"我都諗過 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n但貼左真實感大啲"},{"pid":"d9bdf90cee6435c303056d57ff5f99dfd40d2cbb","tid":618428,"uid":147314,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:25:14.000Z","msg":"Chinese National Gets 10 Years in US Prison for Stealing Trade Secrets<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://gdb.voanews.com/D909335D-D919-4212-9615-CA1120E72745_cx0_cy9_cw0_w200_r1_s.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fgdb.voanews.com%2FD909335D-D919-4212-9615-CA1120E72745_cx0_cy9_cw0_w200_r1_s.jpg&h=ca2382d2&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\nFILE - Zhang Weiqiang is shown in this Wyandotte County, Kansas, Detention Center handout photo released to Reuters Dec. 12, 2013. <span style=\"color: red;\">Zhang is one of two agricultural scientists from China who were charged</span> with trying to steal samples of a variety of seeds from a biopharmaceutical company's research facility in Kansas, said Barry Grissom, spokesman for the U.S. attorney for the District of Kansas.<br />\n<br />\nA Chinese scientist was sentenced Wednesday to more than 10 years in a U.S. federal prison for stealing valuable rice seeds from a Kansas biopharmaceutical firm.<br />\n<br />\nWeiqiang Zhang, a Chinese national who is a permanent legal resident living in Manhattan, Kansas, was convicted last year of conspiracy to steal trade secrets after taking hundreds of rice seeds from his employer, Ventria Bioscience.<br />\n<br />\nVentria genetically programs rice to artificially produce human proteins. The proteins are extracted from the rice and used in drugs and other medical therapies.<br />\n<br />\nU.S. prosecutors said Zhang stole the seeds and stored them at his home. He passed the seeds to visitors from a Chinese crop research center in 2013.<br />\n<br />\nU.S. Customs agents found the seeds in their luggage as they prepared to return to China.<br />\n<br />\nProsecutors said Ventria spent millions of dollars and years of research to perfect methods for extracting proteins from the rice.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;It is vital that we protect such intellectual property from theft and exploitation by foreign interests,&rdquo; U.S. Attorney Stephen McAllister said. &ldquo;We all benefit when American companies continue to drive socially valuable advancements in food, medicine and technology.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.voanews.com/a/chinese-national-sentenced-stealing-trade-secrets/4333322.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.voanews.com%2Fa%2Fchinese-national-sentenced-stealing-trade-secrets%2F4333322.html&d=Qkcn4anxcNjNLEy4KtNlZQEk2Noh57F05xbgvjQdsX8%3D&h=f0245ef6\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.voanews.com/a/chinese-national-sentenced-stealing-trade-secrets/4333322.html</a>"},{"pid":"8826d8f48725291af34970e2b828a5297971d2ab","tid":618428,"uid":110339,"like":77,"dislike":4,"score":73,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:27:04.000Z","msg":"人地無seed都偷番嚟<br />\n唔似d不孝連登仔<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"bfd0dc7f5dc3d7d419871fc7fb4dd5808863252e","tid":618428,"uid":106375,"like":5,"dislike":0,"score":5,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:37:05.000Z","msg":"坐完強制遣返+成世禁止入境就差唔多啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"ed456da6fd25cbe57589dcbaab2296070192b1db","tid":618428,"uid":125809,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:39:32.000Z","msg":"Trump: 我們被中國偷3000億IP<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"cc886270d971c0658f8541368d4d8e9f6f5c7fc1","tid":618428,"uid":66324,"like":25,"dislike":0,"score":25,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-04-05T22:40:05.000Z","msg":"中国人應該係世上唯一唔肯歸化同仲搞緊民族主義的民族 <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" cla